I, David, take you, Angela, to be my Wife, to love unconditionally,
through good times & bad. When we say regretful things when we're
hungry. When my spine inevitably curls over and your stomach stops
working entirely -- My love for you will only grow exponentially.

You have been my example of what being a better person can be. Not just
to other people, but also, and probably more importantly, myself. You
have been my best friend that makes all those *in-between* moments more
interesting and enjoyable by filling the air with random songs or facts,
whether historical or even more-likely, Disney related. You've been my
muse that supports & inspires the creativity in my ridiculous projects &
hobbies in and around the house, no matter how messy or expensive. And
let's be honest; you've also been my therapist, fashion stylist,
life-coach, teacher, personal trainer, barber, baker, interior designer,
occasional chauffer, doctor ..you get it.

I can only try to provide you with all that you have given me, and I
promise I will do my very best, every day.\
\
I Promise to ensure that I offer you the compassion you provide me to
get through the rough days. To give you those extra "little things" to
make the great days even better. I promise to allow you the
peace-of-mind that you allow me. A peace-of-mind that only comes with a
solid foundation of unwavering trust, earned through countless genuine
conversations and heartfelt meaningful moments.

Our time together has been the best years of my life. These years have
also proven to be the most productive and transformative.

We've propagated our future together; Our family is budding, our careers
are blossoming, and now, we're here celebrating the harvest of our love
together.

Angela Celeste Kirsch, I promise I will love you forever, to the stars
and beyond. From this dimension, through the infinite number of others
-- I love you in all of them, infinitely & forever. And I cannot wait to
spend the rest of my life with you.
